  "body": "Hi @slundberg,\r\n\r\nThanks so much for maintaining such an amazing package!!\r\n\r\nThis PR adds display_data functionality for numeric features in scatter plots for variables that have been scaled or transformed. In the current implementation, adding untransformed values to shap_values.display_data produced:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/45714941/107898750-8e23d080-6f0a-11eb-82e9-3b0f27987db8.png)\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/45714941/107898888-e1961e80-6f0a-11eb-950b-b6c086a9cb7f.png)\r\n\r\n￼\r\nThe code in this PR uses the display_data, if available, for the bottom axis, and adds a top axis with the values used in the input:\r\n￼\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/45714941/107898901-e955c300-6f0a-11eb-827e-440accec295f.png)\r\n\r\nOther small fixes include adding cmap inputs into the in-function dependence_legacy calls, as well as specifying the fontdict key directly in set_xticklabels which removes a matplotlib warning.\r\n\r\nI look forward to hearing any thoughts/suggestion!",
